# Multilingual support (i18n)

> **Compliance:** Mandatory (`agents-mandatory.mdc`). Merge blocker for any user-facing copy.

User-facing text must be **fully localized** across every supported locale. i18n is a merge blocker.

## Supported locales (all required for new keys)

Add every new `string name` to **each** directory under `composeApp/src/commonMain/composeResources/`:

| Directory | Language |
|-----------|----------|
| `values` | English (default) |
| `values-fr` | French |
| `values-es` | Spanish |
| `values-de` | German |
| `values-it` | Italian |
| `values-ar` | Arabic |
| `values-ar-rSA` | Arabic (Saudi) |
| `values-nap` | Neapolitan |

Missing a locale fails `*LocaleStringsTest` and ships incomplete UX.

## Where strings live

- **Resources only:** `composeResources/values*/strings.xml`
- **UI:** `stringResource(Res.string.<key>, …)` in `@Composable` functions
- **Never** hardcode user-visible text in composables, screen models, domain, or data
- **Screen models** expose counts/ids/enums; **composables** format snackbars, labels, summaries
- Resolve strings in composable scope — pass `String` into `LaunchedEffect`/callbacks, not `stringResource` inside them

## Key registry & tests

- Register feature keys in `i18n/*StringKeys.kt` (`NutritionStringKeys`, `HomeStringKeys`, `HouseholdStringKeys`, etc.)
- Run `:composeApp:testDebugUnitTest` — includes locale parity suites
- Default `values` strings non-blank; placeholders identical across locales (`%1$d`, `%2$s`, same order)

## Consistency

- Reuse helpers: `nutritionDayLabel()`, shared meal slot keys, `action_back`
- Same terminology in hub, detail screens, and `firebase-appdistribution-testcases.yaml`
- **RTL** (`values-ar*`): logical placeholders; avoid hard-coded LTR-only layouts
- `LanguageManager` / `SupportedAppLanguages` — switching language refreshes visible UI (no cached English)

## Review checklist (before PR)

1. New/changed keys exist in all 8 locale files
2. No new hardcoded UI copy in Kotlin
3. Formatted strings use resources, not `.replace()` hacks
4. Locale tests pass; spot-check English + one RTL locale for layout-sensitive screens
